			<DIV CLASS="Content">
			<table border="0" cellpadding="12" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
				<TR>
					<td valign="top">
<B CLASS="HeadlineText">FAQ -  Homepage</B><BR><B CLASS="SubHeadlineText">Focus Effects</B><UL><img SRC="images/icons/arrowbubble.gif" alt="arrow" WIDTH=13 HEIGHT=13 HSPACE=2 VSPACE=2>&nbsp;<b><A HREF="#11"><u>What do "Distance" Focus Effects do?</u></a></b><br><img SRC="images/icons/arrowbubble.gif" alt="arrow" WIDTH=13 HEIGHT=13 HSPACE=2 VSPACE=2>&nbsp;<b><A HREF="#12"><u>What do "Improved Healing" Focus do?</u></a></b><br><img SRC="images/icons/arrowbubble.gif" alt="arrow" WIDTH=13 HEIGHT=13 HSPACE=2 VSPACE=2>&nbsp;<b><A HREF="#13"><u>What does "Improved Damage" focus do?</u></a></b><br><img SRC="images/icons/arrowbubble.gif" alt="arrow" WIDTH=13 HEIGHT=13 HSPACE=2 VSPACE=2>&nbsp;<b><A HREF="#14"><u>What do "Preservation" Focus effects do?</u></a></b><br><img SRC="images/icons/arrowbubble.gif" alt="arrow" WIDTH=13 HEIGHT=13 HSPACE=2 VSPACE=2>&nbsp;<b><A HREF="#15"><u>What do "Spell Haste" Focus Effects do?</u></a></b><br></UL><BR><HR><A NAME="11"><b>Q:&nbsp;What do "Distance" Focus Effects do?</b></A><p><b>A:</b>&nbsp;Distance Focus Effects, which include such names, but are not limited to, Druzzil's Distance, Extended Range 1-4, etc, increase the range in which spells may be cast.  The exact value of range increase, and the level of spells effected is listed on Lucy (www.fnord.lucy.net), as they are greatly variable based on the focus.<br>
<center><br><a href="#TOP"><img alt="Back to top" BORDER=0 src="Images/icons/TopArrow.gif" WIDTH=13 HEIGHT=13><br>Top</a></CENTER><HR><A NAME="12"><b>Q:&nbsp;What do "Improved Healing" Focus do?</b></A><p><b>A:</b>&nbsp;Improved Healing Focus, which includes effects like, Marr's Gift, Improved Healing 1-4, etc, gives the chance for heals above their normal amount they would heal.  Such as, an item that normally heals for 100, with a focus that increases it 10%, has a chance to heal up to 110 instead.  An important note on this focus.  While the maximum amount that it is adjusted is Fixed (such as Marr's Gift is capped at 25%), the actual amount it gives per heal is random up to that cap.  For exact details on what level spells are healed, and what percentage the heal bonus is, refer to Lucy.<br>
<center><br><a href="#TOP"><img alt="Back to top" BORDER=0 src="Images/icons/TopArrow.gif" WIDTH=13 HEIGHT=13><br>Top</a></CENTER><HR><A NAME="13"><b>Q:&nbsp;What does "Improved Damage" focus do?</b></A><p><b>A:</b>&nbsp;Improved Damage Focus, which includes, Improved Damage 1-4, Fury of Ro, Wrath of Eci, Druzzil's Fury, etc, increases the amount of damage, any Direct Damage can do that falls into its parameters.  There are 2 general types of Improved Damage Focus'.  1.)  General:  These affect all Direct Damage spells, however, as a counter, they often do not give nearly the same increase chance as a Specialized Focus.  2.) Specialized:  These will only give a bonus to certain types of Direct Damage, based on the focus (Examples:  Fury of Ro only affects Fire Nukes, Wrath of Eci only affects Cold, the effects on all &quot;Caster Class&quot; Elemental Guantlets, affects only 1 particular spell, etc)  However, because of the more specialized nature, these often offer much greater bonus' to damage done.  One important note on these Focus Effects:  The exact bonus when a spell is cast, is Random, up to it max effect.  For the exact Maximum bonus, Levels affected, and potential limitations and/or restrictions on Improved Damage Foci, please refer to Lucy.<br>
<center><br><a href="#TOP"><img alt="Back to top" BORDER=0 src="Images/icons/TopArrow.gif" WIDTH=13 HEIGHT=13><br>Top</a></CENTER><HR><A NAME="14"><b>Q:&nbsp;What do "Preservation" Focus effects do?</b></A><p><b>A:</b>&nbsp;These focus effects, which include Mana Preservation 1-4, Conservation of Solusek, Preservation of Xegony, etc, reduce the amount of mana Spells cost to cast.  These fall into 2 catagories of effects:  1.)  General:  These affect all spells cast, however, due to the all inclusive nature, often do not offer nearly as much benefit as specialized focus effects.  2.)  Specialized:  These focus effects are designed to only affect certain types of spells (Examples, Conservation of Solusek only affects Offensive Spells), while they are much more narrow use than General Foci, they offer much greater benefits for those spells that do fit in their parameters.  For the exact details on Spell Level Requirements, Potential Limitations/Restrictions, and what the exact % of mana saved on each cast is, please refer to Lucy.<br>
<center><br><a href="#TOP"><img alt="Back to top" BORDER=0 src="Images/icons/TopArrow.gif" WIDTH=13 HEIGHT=13><br>Top</a></CENTER><HR><A NAME="15"><b>Q:&nbsp;What do "Spell Haste" Focus Effects do?</b></A><p><b>A:</b>&nbsp;Spell Haste Focus Effects, which include Spell Haste 1-4, Haste of Mithaniel, Speed of Solusect, etc, reduce the casting time on spells by a set percentage. Like most focus effects, there are two major categories of these. 1.) General: These Focus effects, affect all spells cast by the wearer, however, due to the generalized nature, the exact percentage of haste is often lower than Specialized Foci. 2.) Specialized: These Focus effects, affect only certain types of spells (Examples, Haste of MIthaniel only effects beneficial spells, Speed of Solusek only affects Offensive Spells), because of the specialized nature however, they often give greater spell haste percentages, then their more Generalized relations. For details on affected spell levels, exact haste percentage, and potential Limitations/Restrictions, please refer to Lucy.<br>
